codex
I’ve isolated the main execution bug. The verifier only tries flash-funded paths when `TARGET_MARKET.getCash()` is already nonzero, but the redeem and borrow PoC can bootstrap that cash with the flashloan itself, so the profitable path is being skipped at block `17620870`. I’m patching the verifier to size funding from external liquidity and to scan dynamic Bao markets for the reentrant victim leg.
2026-05-19T05:43:30.912073Z ERROR codex_core::tools::router: error=apply_patch verification failed: Failed to find expected lines in /Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/cases/bao/src/src/FlawVerifier.sol:
        address[] memory markets = _candidateMarkets();
        if (markets.length == 0) {
            return (false, address(0), address(0));
        }
codex
The patch needs to be narrower against the current file shape. I’m re-reading the exact function bodies in `src/FlawVerifier.sol` and then applying the runtime fix directly.
